            "body": "@justinmk My example: I want to support running denols in single-file mode for typescript files outside of js/ts projects, and in root_dir mode for regular deno projects, but also run tsserver in single-file mode for javascript files and all other non-deno projects.\r\n\r\nContext: one of Deno's unique qualities is its import behavior -- modules can be referenced by URL in the `import` statement so you don't need a package.json. Makes it very convenient to just script something in a `.ts` file somewhere -- one of ryan's initial intentions for the project IIRC from the original announcement talk.",
